  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Partnership for responsible cobalt sourcing</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will focus on artisanally mined cobalt. Cobalt is one of the key materials used in batteries for multiple applications, including smartphones (Lithium- Ion batteries) and lighting products. The project partners are Fairphone, Signify, Huayou and The Impact Facility.The CSR risks that this project aims to address are:1) Health and Safety at work: very poor working conditions of artisanal miners at both Kasulu and Kamilombe ASM mine sites, which are (mainly) the result of the informality with which ASM mining has evolved in the DR Congo.2) Discrimination &amp; gender: Women working at ASM sites have no access to safety equipment and are commonly restricted to low-skill activities such as washing ore and as such earning the least, as well as working under hazardous conditions.3) Market distortion &amp; competition: dominant sense by the ASM miners of dishonest and intransparent trading terms of cobalt traders due to a) an asymmetry to access to information and a lack of clear mechanisms to communicate effectively between cooperative and miners.The project therefore aims to 1) show demand for fairly sourced ASM Cobalt by integrating it in the supply chains of the project partners Huayou, Signify and Fairphone and 2) by mobilizing the industry to follow this example, acknowledging the need to invest in and accept Fair ASM cobalt in their supply chains. The project will therefore actively coordinate and align with industry and other key stakeholder initiatives and efforts in the cobalt (battery) industry.</narrative>
  </description>
